Text Review:
Staff are unaware about policies; Booked this place 6 months in advance for our wedding night and the staff informed us that we can click wedding pictures at nights and was confirmed by Numerous staff including their managers;
At the last moment the hotel Staff now tells us that we cant click any photos and denying that they said it; All our plans have to be now changed;
Would not reccomed this hotel where the staff provide wrong information; We wanted to have our stay here as this was the place me and my wife first meet;

We stayed at Alila Diwa Goa in May 2012. We landed in Goa early and reached the hotel by 6 a.m. and were promptly shown to our room. 

When we entered the room (341), my wife noticed that the floor was dirty so we requested that the room be cleaned. 

While we were waiting for the room to be cleaned, my wife opened one of the draws and pulled at what she thought was a hair dryer - not only did the hair dryer pull back but it was also furry. She pulled away with a shriek. The rat in the draw (which was one fat bugger) was moving around slowly. By this time the attendant came back to the room and when we told him that there was a rat in the draw, he promptly opened the draw and started shooting a video on his mobile - this would have made us furious if it wasn't so ridiculous. I also snapped a pic of the rat (see pics)!

We called the manager, who was unavailable as he was on Holiday. The Assistant Manager came to meet us and upgraded us to a suite in the Diwa Wing (no big deal) and offered us complimentary breakfast (which was a part of our package anyway!!). The rest of the stay was uneventful. 

Other than the big [--] rat, following are my thoughts on the property: 
(A) The Property looks very good - not really a five star though;
(B) Breakfast is good; 
(C) The Diwa Wing Pool is very nice; 
(D) Close to Martin's Corner - so you needn't worry about eating good food; 
(E) Quite a distance from the beach (not a pleasant walk in Goa heat) - the hotel organizes and pick up and drop though. 

Our experience at Alila is a stark contrast to the other hotel experiences that we have had in Goa - where we have more often than not been wowed by the rooms and the service.
